 The Fiat Panda gathering in Pandino beat all records to become the biggest Panda meeting in the world. The guest of honour was the new Panda Waze, the first city car to proudly display the Waze name and integrate the Waze navigation app into the Panda Uconnect app, as well as being the most socially connected Panda ever. Read more: Fuel increase: Why Lowvelders pay more than the rest of SA  Read more: Little Suzuki gets a new look The colourful crew of Fiat Pandas, counting many one-of-a-kind versions, met in front of Pandino Castle and 200 cars spelled out the words “Panda Waze”. 